The paper deals with the problem of recovering signals from their power spectral density, which is a problem in signal processing. The paper specifically focuses on the case where the underlying signals are sparse. Therefore, cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of semidefinite programming (SDP) and reweighted $l_1$-minimization, which are optimization techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the design of measurement matrices, which is a topic in compressed sensing, making cs.SI (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
